Description: Add cuda-nvml-dev-13-2 build-dep and drop apt libpmix-dev.
 cuda-nvml-dev-13-2 ships nvml.h at /usr/local/cuda/include/nvml.h and a
 link-time libnvidia-ml.so stub under /usr/local/cuda/lib64/stubs, which
 is what Slurm's --with-nvml=/usr/local/cuda configure flag consumes to
 enable the mpi/gpu_nvml autodetect plugin at build time (runtime
 libnvidia-ml.so.1 is injected by nvidia-container-toolkit from the host
 driver). libpmix-dev is removed because PMIx is provided by the AWS EFA
 installer at /opt/amazon/pmix (see debian/rules --with-pmix= patch);
 shipping both apt libpmix and the EFA PMIx tree would create an
 ABI-conflicting second PMIx tree.
Author: meshy-dev
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-04-19
--- a/debian/control
+++ b/debian/control
@@ -14,6 +14,7 @@ Build-Depends:
  libgtk2.0-dev,
  libhdf5-dev,
  libhttp-parser-dev,
+ cuda-nvml-dev-13-2,
  libhwloc-dev,
  libipmimonitoring-dev,
  libjson-c-dev,
@@ -25,7 +26,6 @@ Build-Depends:
  libncurses-dev,
  libpam0g-dev,
  libperl-dev,
- libpmix-dev,
  librdkafka-dev,
  librrd-dev,
  libyaml-dev,
